01:07.737 --> 01:10.606
Yeah. We have a man shot
in the bodega

01:10.608 --> 01:12.875
at the corner of Clarkson
and 83rd.

01:12.877 --> 01:15.344
Okay, so we work
the same M.O. as that one.

01:15.346 --> 01:17.313
Detectives, this
is Liza Daniels.

01:17.315 --> 01:19.215
She asked to
speak with you.

01:19.217 --> 01:20.316
Okay, make it quick.

01:20.318 --> 01:21.850
You know Emily Harrison?

01:21.852 --> 01:23.886
We're familiar
with her, yeah.

01:23.888 --> 01:25.254
Emily's a friend.

01:25.256 --> 01:27.990
At least she was until I started
dating her ex-boyfriend.

01:27.992 --> 01:30.326
- Brandon Mitchell?
- Emily said

01:30.328 --> 01:31.427
some horrible things about him.

01:31.429 --> 01:33.095
When I said
I didn't believe her,

01:33.097 --> 01:34.730
she said I should talk to you.

01:34.732 --> 01:36.932
He's not a good guy. You
should stay away from him.

01:36.934 --> 01:38.534
How about that?

01:38.536 --> 01:40.869
Why don't you take
a look at these?

01:40.871 --> 01:43.205
Go ahead.

01:48.878 --> 01:52.448
He handcuffed her,
then he beat her and raped her.

01:52.450 --> 01:55.351
Brandon couldn't have done that.

01:55.353 --> 01:57.353
- Why not?
- Because Brandon's not like that.

01:57.355 --> 01:59.622
And if he had done
that, he'd be in jail.

01:59.624 --> 02:01.223
Doesn't always work that way.

02:01.225 --> 02:03.792
Brandon's a great guy.

02:03.794 --> 02:05.127
Emily is my problem.

02:05.129 --> 02:06.562
How's that?

02:06.564 --> 02:07.963
She's calling me every day.

02:07.965 --> 02:10.699
She even came by my office
acting like a jealous psycho.

02:10.701 --> 02:14.169
Trust me, Emily does
not want Brandon back.

02:14.171 --> 02:17.139
Look... you guys know her.

02:17.141 --> 02:20.476
Sounds like she'll listen to
you, so do her a favor, please.

02:20.478 --> 02:22.444
Tell her that if she
doesn't back off,

02:22.446 --> 02:24.413
I'm gonna file a
harassment complaint.

02:32.255 --> 02:34.556
Super said there was a homeless
person living down here.

02:34.558 --> 02:35.557
Ooh.

02:36.794 --> 02:39.061
Wait. Hang on.

02:42.066 --> 02:43.599
Hold on.

02:46.803 --> 02:48.771
I'll pick up your dry cleaning.

02:48.773 --> 02:50.773
Um, you have

02:50.775 --> 02:53.142
lunch at Babbo at 12:30,

02:53.144 --> 02:55.077
and then meetings back to back

02:55.079 --> 02:56.679
before the Met reception.

02:56.681 --> 02:59.615
Got it.

02:59.617 --> 03:01.083
Yeah.

03:04.387 --> 03:05.220
What's your name?

03:05.222 --> 03:06.255
Tara Chandler.

03:06.257 --> 03:07.756
How long have you been
living here?

03:07.758 --> 03:09.091
Five days.

03:09.093 --> 03:10.659
I used to live upstairs in 12E,

03:10.661 --> 03:12.294
but my roommates
and I got evicted.

03:12.296 --> 03:12.958
Why?

03:12.982 --> 03:14.230
Seven of us living
in a two-bedroom.

03:14.231 --> 03:16.265
Only way we could
afford the place.

03:16.267 --> 03:18.801
How are you living here?

03:18.803 --> 03:20.369
Um,

03:20.371 --> 03:23.172
I still have
my laundry room key, and

03:23.174 --> 03:24.373
there's a shower in there.

03:24.375 --> 03:27.343
There's power.
I get cell reception.

03:27.345 --> 03:28.877
View kind of sucks, but...

03:28.879 --> 03:30.279
Sounds like
you still have a job.

03:30.281 --> 03:31.413
Why haven't you found
a new place?

03:31.415 --> 03:33.182
Manhattan rents are insane.

03:33.184 --> 03:34.149
What about your roommates?

03:34.151 --> 03:35.484
They're all moving to Queens.

03:35.486 --> 03:36.585
What's wrong with Queens?

03:36.587 --> 03:38.287
My boss is Camilla Lawson,

03:38.289 --> 03:40.589
the president of Chadway Dunce,
the publishing house.

03:40.591 --> 03:42.257
She's seriously
high maintenance.

03:42.259 --> 03:44.059
Insists her assistant
live in Manhattan

03:44.061 --> 03:46.995
and be on call 24-7
for $800 a week.

03:46.997 --> 03:48.931
Maybe you should find a new job.

03:48.933 --> 03:52.167
300 people applied for
this position, and 300 people

03:52.169 --> 03:53.802
are waiting if I mess up.
- Okay.

03:53.804 --> 03:55.070
Can't you crash
with family or friends

03:55.072 --> 03:56.271
till you find a new place?

03:56.273 --> 03:58.640
I just moved here
from Scranton nine months ago.

03:58.642 --> 04:01.043
I work all the time.
I don't have time for friends.

04:01.045 --> 04:03.612
Okay, we can see
you're in a tough spot, but...

04:03.614 --> 04:05.147
you're trespassing.

04:05.149 --> 04:06.749
So we can let you off

04:06.751 --> 04:09.218
with a warning today,
but you can't stay here.

04:09.220 --> 04:11.553
I understand. Thank you.

04:11.555 --> 04:13.989
I'll get all of my stuff
out of here right after work.

04:15.525 --> 04:18.560
If we can help with anything
else, give us a call.

04:20.363 --> 04:22.431
<i>And a big</i>

04:22.433 --> 04:25.267
thank you from the Chief
Constable of Scotland

04:25.269 --> 04:27.002
for showing him and
his people around.

04:27.004 --> 04:28.270
Don't remind me.

04:28.272 --> 04:30.172
What's the problem?
They said they learned a lot.

04:30.174 --> 04:31.373
Yeah, I learned something, too.

04:31.375 --> 04:32.841
Never drink with Scottish cops.

04:32.843 --> 04:34.009
We have

04:34.011 --> 04:36.078
a problem with
the bodega robbery in Brooklyn.

04:36.080 --> 04:37.913
Yeah, I got word
shopkeeper didn't make it.

04:37.915 --> 04:39.782
- Yeah.
- Yeah. There's more bad news.

04:39.784 --> 04:41.250
According
to the <i>Post</i> Web site,

04:41.252 --> 04:42.818
there was a customer
named James Reed

04:42.820 --> 04:44.620
in the shop at the
time of the shooting.

04:44.622 --> 04:46.355
And?

04:46.357 --> 04:48.690
Reed is a sergeant at the 3-6.

04:48.692 --> 04:50.225
He didn't lift a finger

04:50.227 --> 04:51.693
to help this guy.

04:51.695 --> 04:52.928
He failed to take any action?

04:52.930 --> 04:55.130
He called 911
after the perps fled.

04:55.132 --> 04:56.265
And he was he armed at the time?

04:56.267 --> 04:57.466
According to the <i>Post,</i>

04:57.468 --> 04:58.667
he was carrying
an off-duty revolver.

04:58.669 --> 05:00.035
And I assume they used

05:00.037 --> 05:01.737
their usual editorial restraint?

05:01.739 --> 05:04.206
"Coward Cop Ducks and Covers."

05:04.208 --> 05:06.542
Reed's C.O.

05:06.544 --> 05:08.177
says he wasn't alone
at the bodega.

05:08.179 --> 05:11.580
He was with
his ten-year-old daughter.

05:13.183 --> 05:15.918
That changes everything.

05:15.920 --> 05:17.753
Actually, it's neither
here nor there.

05:17.755 --> 05:18.821
What's that mean?

05:18.823 --> 05:20.989
It means it's not
as simple as that.

05:20.991 --> 05:23.826
Damn it!

05:23.828 --> 05:27.062
He was with his daughter,
and off-duty.

05:27.064 --> 05:29.431
And every cop takes an oath
to uphold the law.

05:29.433 --> 05:30.899
There's not a time clock on it.

05:30.901 --> 05:33.335
You don't punch out
from that commitment.

05:33.337 --> 05:34.770
It was Reed's duty to act,

05:34.772 --> 05:37.139
to somehow come to the aid
of that crime victim.

05:37.141 --> 05:39.575
Did the <i>Post</i> know,
or did they just leave it out?

05:39.577 --> 05:41.743
There's no headline
if you include the kid.

05:41.745 --> 05:43.679
Yeah.

05:43.681 --> 05:46.114
What do you want us to do, boss?

05:46.116 --> 05:47.883
What I want to do is

05:47.885 --> 05:50.385
make them have all the facts
before they print something.

05:50.387 --> 05:54.323
What I have to do,
now that it's out there?

05:54.325 --> 05:59.194
Tell his C.O. I want to see
Officer Reed up here forthwith.

